&lt;h3 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Intro 
    &lt;div id=&#34;intro&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have always wanted to use cool animated wallpapers on Linux. Found many free ways, but nothing rivaled the awesome features of &lt;a
  href=&#34;https://www.wallpaperengine.io/en&#34;
    target=&#34;_blank&#34;
  &gt;Wallpaper Engine&lt;/a&gt; found on steam for the low price of $5.. Only problem was that it only ran on Windows, nothing else. But someone awesome took it upon him/herself to port it over to Linux.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Below is a video on how to get it running on KDE Plasma via that plugin&amp;hellip; Just note that, as it&amp;rsquo;s mentioned in the video, not all animated wallpapers will work, test it and see. Oh and any Audio Spectrum ones that are supposed to react to music will absolutely not work as it has no way to hook to players. Besides that it should work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&#34;position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;&#34;&gt;
